.TH "batadv_forw_packet_bcasts_left" 9 "batadv_forw_packet_bcasts_left" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
batadv_forw_packet_bcasts_left \- check if a retransmission is necessary
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" batadv_forw_packet_bcasts_left
.BI "(struct batadv_forw_packet *forw_packet "  ","
.BI "struct batadv_hard_iface *hard_iface "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "forw_packet" 12
the forwarding packet to check
.IP "hard_iface" 12
the interface to check on
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Checks whether a given packet has any (re)transmissions left on the provided
interface.

hard_iface may be NULL: In that case the number of transmissions this skb had
so far is compared with the maximum amount of retransmissions independent of
any interface instead.
.SH "RETURN"
True if (re)transmissions are left, false otherwise.
